Document: ShapeCast3D
Path: godot/classes/class_shapecast3d.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of the ShapeCast3D node, including collision settings, debug visualization, and shape configuration.

- **collide_with_areas** (bool): If true, collisions with Area3Ds will be reported. Default: false.
  - Method: set_collide_with_areas(value: bool)
  - Method: is_collide_with_areas_enabled()
- **collide_with_bodies** (bool): If true, collisions with PhysicsBody3Ds will be reported. Default: true.
  - Method: set_collide_with_bodies(value: bool)
  - Method: is_collide_with_bodies_enabled()
- **collision_mask** (int): The shape's collision mask. Only objects in at least one collision layer enabled in the mask will be detected. See Collision layers and masks in the documentation for more information. Default: 1.
  - Method: set_collision_mask(value: int)
  - Method: get_collision_mask()
- **collision_result** (Array): Returns the complete collision information from the collision sweep. The data returned is the same as in the PhysicsDirectSpaceState3D.get_rest_info() method. Default: [].
  - Method: get_collision_result()
- **debug_shape_custom_color** (Color): The custom color to use to draw the shape in the editor and at run-time if Visible Collision Shapes is enabled in the Debug menu. This color will be highlighted at run-time if the ShapeCast3D is colliding with something. If set to Color(0.0, 0.0, 0.0) (by default), the color set in ProjectSettings.debug/shapes/collision/shape_color is used. Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1).
  - Method: set_debug_shape_custom_color(value: Color)
  - Method: get_debug_shape_custom_color()
- **enabled** (bool): If true, collisions will be reported. Default: true.
  - Method: set_enabled(value: bool)
  - Method: is_enabled()
- **exclude_parent** (bool): If true, the parent node will be excluded from collision detection. Default: true.
  - Method: set_exclude_parent_body(value: bool)
  - Method: get_exclude_parent_body()
- **margin** (float): The collision margin for the shape. A larger margin helps detecting collisions more consistently, at the cost of precision. Default: 0.0.
  - Method: set_margin(value: float)
  - Method: get_margin()
- **max_results** (int): The number of intersections can be limited with this parameter, to reduce the processing time. Default: 32.
  - Method: set_max_results(value: int)
  - Method: get_max_results()
- **shape** (Shape3D): The shape to be used for collision queries.
  - Method: set_shape(value: Shape3D)
  - Method: get_shape()
- **target_position** (Vector3): The shape's destination point, relative to this node's Node3D.position. Default: Vector3(0, -1, 0).
  - Method: set_target_position(value: Vector3)
  - Method: get_target_position()
